[2026-03-18T17:40:37.630Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n\n## REQUIREMENT\n\n# Replace linear if/else route chain with Map lookup\n\n## Metadata\n- **Category**: performance\n- **Effort**: Unknown (4/3)\n- **Impact**: Unknown (5/3)\n- **Scan Type**: perf_optimizer\n- **Generated**: 3/17/2026, 11:25:13 PM\n\n## Description\nhttpApi.ts routes requests through 30+ chained if/else-if blocks with string operations (startsWith, endsWith, replace) evaluated sequentially on every request. Refactor to a Map<string, Handler> for exact-match routes and a small sorted array for parameterized routes. This reduces routing from O(n) string comparisons to O(1) map lookup for most requests.\n\n## Reasoning\nThe current routing evaluates up to 30 conditions per request, each doing multiple string operations. As more endpoints are added this grows linearly. A map-based router is both faster and more maintainable, eliminating the fragile pattern of negated endsWith checks that are a source of bugs when new sub-routes are added.\n\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\nUse Claude Code skills as appropriate for implementation guidance. Check `.claude/skills/` directory for available skills.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\n   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\n   - title: 2-6 word summary\n   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done\n   - category: one of feature/bugfix/refactor/performance/security/infrastructure/ui/docs/test\n   - patternsApplied: comma-separated patterns used (e.g. \"repository pattern, debounce, memoization\")\n\n2. Verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` (fix any type errors)\n\nBegin implementation now."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"040eddb1-cf36-46d8-994d-56417dba528b","uuid":"ad597e6e-51eb-4c25-a6a0-76b01da04848","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:40:37.546Z","isSynthetic":true}
